      <p class="article-subtitle">You finish a movie you hate because you already paid. You stay in a job for another year because you've given it five. You keep funding a failing project because walking away feels like admitting defeat. This is the sunk cost fallacy — and it costs far more than you think.</p>
      <div class="author-info">
